Headlines.SeoHeadline: HEARD ON THE STREET: Sacred Tablets
Headlines.Headline: Sacred Tablets

PARAGRAPH.#text: Most people think Ben Bernanke pilots a helicopter. But Google had him in a stealth bomber Wednesday. The Federal Reserve chief gave no sign of dumping more money on markets, provoking modest drop in stocks. But around 6 p.m., Google Finance's website showed the Dow down by no less than 100%. Now that is a real flash crash.Losing your C-suite job? At least you can keep your Angry Birds. The filings experts at Footnoted have ferreted out a new trend in severance perks: hanging on to the company iPad. The latest example is Advanced Analogic Technologies, whose departing finance chief, Brian McDonald, was promised a new Apple tablet as long as he turned in his old one. Footnoted found similar perks at General Growth Properties, Medtronic, Scotts Miracle-Gro and TD Ameritrade, among others. For executives who make millions, it seems a bit like grabbing a box of paper clips on the way out the door. Another example of corporate America's attitude: iTake because iCan.
